####STEP 2 Check for duplicate IDs. Subset baseline data
#Note: ABCD 2.0.1. contains duplicate IDs due to having both baseline and 1 year follow-up data
# column: "eventname" signifies study wave (e.g., baseline, 1 year follow-up etc.)


nrow(pds_tidy) #check number of rows
## [1] 16826
n_distinct(pds_tidy$src_subject_id, na.rm = F) #check for duplicates 
## [1] 11875
                                                #length(unique(pds_tidy$src_subject_id)) 
                                                #can also use this code. 


distinct(as.data.frame(pds_tidy$eventname)) #gives levels in eventname column
##         pds_tidy$eventname
## 1    baseline_year_1_arm_1
## 2 1_year_follow_up_y_arm_1
pds_bl_tidy <- subset(pds_tidy, eventname=="baseline_year_1_arm_1") #subset baseline (bl) data
filter(pds_bl_tidy, eventname == "1_year_follow_up_y_arm_1") #check follow up (1_year_follow_up_y_arm_1) data removed

####STEP 4: Split dataset by sex to generate PDS total scores. 
#remove NAs in other columns after dataframe is split. Easier to do because of natural NA values
#for PDS items of opposite sex. 
#all NAs were removed at this stage. 

####MALES Total N = 6,163 ------- Complete cases = 5,732

PDS_M <- filter(pds_bl_tidy, sex == 1) #df with males only
PDS_M <- PDS_M %>% 
  select(-c(11:12)) #drop cols for female PDS items
PDS_M <- na.omit(PDS_M) #remove all NAs

PDS_M <- PDS_M %>%
  mutate(
    PDS_M_tot = rowSums(PDS_M[, c(6,7,8,9,10)]) #generate PDS total score for males. 
  )
colnames(PDS_M) #check new variable exists

  select(-c(9:10)) #drop cols for male PDS items
PDS_F <- na.omit(PDS_F) #remove all NAs

PDS_F <- PDS_F %>%
  mutate(
    PDS_F_tot = rowSums(PDS_F[, c(6,7,8,9,10)]) #generate PDS total score for females. 
  )
colnames(PDS_M) #check new variable exists

#### STEP 6 Generate Pubertal Timing score
#PDS total score was regressed on age for girls and boys separately
#standardised residual obtained was used as the pubertal timing measure.

# load packages for results tables
library(jtools) #great package for summarising regression results

#First plot PDS total and age
#scatter.smooth(x=PDS_M$PDS_M_tot, y=PDS_M$age_years, main="age_years ~ PDS_M_tot")


#### Male pubertal timing linear model ####
#model summary
PT_M <- lm(PDS_M_tot~age_years, data = PDS_M) #linear model
summ(PT_M,
     robust = TRUE, #robust standard error = HC3 as per sandwich package
     scale = TRUE,  #scaled beta used
     confint = TRUE, digits = 3) #get confidence intervals. 95% CI by default )
